SPS encryption functions

Source: R/spsClasses.R
spsEncryption.Rd

Methods in this class can help admin to encrypt files been output from sps. For now it is only used to encypt and decrypt snapshots. This class requires the SPS database. This class inherits all functions from the spsDb class, so there is no need to initiate the spsDb container.

This class is required to run a SPS app. This class needs to be initialized global level. This has already been written in global.R for you.

Method encrypt()

Examples

dir.create("config", showWarnings = FALSE)
spsOption('verbose', TRUE)
my_ecpt <- spsEncryption$new()

#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 Created SPS encryption method container
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 This container inherits all functions from spsDb class
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 Db connected
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 Default SPS-db found and is working
my_ecpt$createDb()

#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 Db connected
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 Creating SPS db...
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 Db write the meta table
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 Db write the raw table
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 Key generated and stored in db
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 Db create admin account
#> [SPS-DANGER] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 Done, Db created at 'config/sps.db'. DO NOT share this file with others or upload to open access domains.
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 Key md5 3c0777223100af88f098d3c0fc65872c
# Read carefully before change the key
my_ecpt$keyChange()

#> [SPS-DANGER] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 
#> change this key will result all accounts' password failed to
#> authenticate. You have to regenerate all password for all
#> accounts. All encrypted file using the old key will fail to
#> decrypt. There is NO way to RECOVER the old key, password
#> and files. If you wish to continue, recall this function
#> with `confirm = TRUE`.
# confirm
my_ecpt$keyChange(confirm = TRUE)

#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:26 Db connected
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:27 You new key has been generated and saved in db
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:27 md5 9b98b3ad39aa7221214424bd2103c7be
# imagine a file has one line "test"
writeLines(text = "test", con = "test.txt")
# encrypt the file
my_ecpt$encrypt("test.txt", "test.bin", overwrite = TRUE)

#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:27 Db connected
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:27 Query sent
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:27 OpenSSL key found md59b98b3ad39aa7221214424bd2103c7be
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:27 Data encrypted
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:27 File write to /home/runner/work/systemPipeShiny/systemPipeShiny/docs/reference/test.bin
# decrypt the file
my_ecpt$decrypt("test.bin", "test_decpt.txt", overwrite = TRUE)

#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:27 File read into memory
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:27 Db connected
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:27 Query sent
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:27 OpenSSL key found md59b98b3ad39aa7221214424bd2103c7be
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:27 Data decrypted
#> [SPS-INFO] 2021-03-30 02:32:27 File write to /home/runner/work/systemPipeShiny/systemPipeShiny/docs/reference/test_decpt.txt
# check the decrypted file content
readLines('test_decpt.txt')

#> [1] "test"
